> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wandork>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 861<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/03 3:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2878.topic>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Cummulative taunt?</span><hr size=1> What disadvantages can you think of if the taunt button where to add a cummulative amount of hate, rather than putting the taunter 1 point above the top agro on the hate list? Does this make sense and would it be more effective than the way taunt works now? Say a successful taunt adds 100 (random number, could be adjeusted for balance of course) hate to the taunter? Thoughts? Ideas? <p><div align="center" class="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial">
<img src="http://www.bfdesigns.net/eq/Wandor_sig.jpg"><br>
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=312001"><b>Wandor</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102" target="_blank"><b>Moordian</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=353608" target="_blank"><b>Wandorfu</b></a></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=besrikarle>Besrikarle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 242<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/03 4:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2878.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Eggplant</span><hr size=1> Easy, someone out aggroes you by a large ammount and your not gonna have a chance to save him. Say shaman slows dots does a few partial cheals and something else and numerically is 1000 ahead of you. You could have a CHANCE and gain aggro with normal taunt, or succesfully taunt and simply add hate, which won't be enough to turn the mob to you. <br>
<br>
That and it would cause people to constantly mash, and that is retarded, and something I dont want to have to do. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilzalot>Kilzalot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 456<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/03 5:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2878.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Eggplant</span><hr size=1> Also, If you are in a CH rotation situation and one MT dies, it would mke switching to the next one basically impossible. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->[65 Overlord]<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=132589">Veteran Kilzalot Drachonis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Member of:<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.blackcompany.cc">The Black Company</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=335271">Rubik Dashammybot</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/03 1:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2878.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cummulative taunt?</span><hr size=1> Making taunt add a fixed number has two effects.<br>
<br>
First it would make it impossible for someone new to pickup aggro (if AE Taunt is also modified to work the same way) when MT dies.  I suppose you can work out something like backup tanks taunt 3/4th as often as MT or something but in that case you just add more hassle anyway, since the existing AE taunt already works.  Like some mentioned, it'd make it impossible to pull slow aggro off a slower.<br>
<br>
The second effect is that once you have aggro you'd pretty much never lose it because you'll just hit that taunt button as often as it refreshes.  Unless the amount added is next to nothing (which Warriors get serverely nerfed since our old taunt is actually quite good), whoever's tanking's going to end up with aggro that comes off too easily.<br>
<br>
Neither of these effects are desirable which is why it's unlikely to happen. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=swiftsoul>Swiftsoul </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/03 1:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2878.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   taunt</span><hr size=1> or you could do both.  <br>
<br>
Chance of All or nothing taunt and a specific hate increaser, which gives the warrior the option of saving taunt to take it from a caster, or once he has established taunt, to build upon it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/03 3:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2878.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cummulative taunt?</span><hr size=1> Making taunt do both would be way too good.  Not going to happen.  It'll also make Taunt totally a button mashing.  Granted taunt isn't exactly rocket science but right now there are at least reasons not to push taunt every chance you get.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dakkin2>Dakkin2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/03 6:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2878.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cummulative taunt?</span><hr size=1> Warriors already have slam/kick to add fixed amounts of hate.  Taunt has a separate valuable use but problem is it doesn't ever work reliably.<br>
<br>
Would it be unbalancing to give warrior taunt a near 100% effectiveness the FIRST time you use it on any mob?<br>
<br>
Just a thought; then perhaps it could be used to get aggro back from slows, to taunt mezzed mobs or if not needed for that to rescue a caster.  You'd have to save it up and use it strategically though since it would only work this way once per fight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=slowmotionz>Slowmotionz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/03 12:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2878.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/eq/Slowmotionz/fullsize/c_warrior.gif WIDTH=71 HEIGHT=177></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cummulative taunt?</span><hr size=1> Taunt should work like this...<br>
<br>
If not top of agro list then it should bring you to TopAgro+1(or whaver number it uses now).<br>
<br>
If top of agro list then add (Taunt Skill) hate. (This means 240 Hate everytime you mash the button at 60+) <p>Slowmotionz Unstopable<br>
